"Zeier M., Mandelbaum A.","Hantavirus-induced acute renal failure [Hantavirus-infektion und akutes nierenversagen]",1999,"Nieren- und Hochdruckkrankheiten","28","3",,"109","113",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0032929541&partnerID=40&md5=07e33d099c5445bb4989050dcbdfa8b2","Medizinische Klinik, Sektion Nephrologie, Universität Heidelberg, Germany; Medizinische Klinik, Sektion Nephrologie, Universität Heidelberg, Bergheimer Straße 56a, D-69115 Heidelberg, Germany","Zeier, M., Medizinische Klinik, Sektion Nephrologie, Universität Heidelberg, Germany, Medizinische Klinik, Sektion Nephrologie, Universität Heidelberg, Bergheimer Straße 56a, D-69115 Heidelberg, Germany; Mandelbaum, A., Medizinische Klinik, Sektion Nephrologie, Universität Heidelberg, Germany","Recently hantavirus-infection and acute renal failure has become more important in almost all countries of Middle- and Northern Europe (nephropathia epidemica). In this part of Europe the course of the disease is commonly mild as compared to hantavirus-infection in South-East Asia and the Balkan. Recently a new subtype of hantavirus-infection with acute pulmonary syndrome has been documented in the United States, a disease with acute pulmonary distress and high mortality. Intensive investigations of nephropathia epidemica in Europe has also shown that pulmonary infiltrates are more common than noted in the past. The distribution of the virus is dependent on the rodent population (vector) and may change with global warming since rodent population may progressively increase. In Argentina a person-to-person transmission of the hantavirus subtype (Andes) was documented recently and may influence the management of the hantavirus- infected patient in the future. In summary one should always be cautious in regard to hantavirus-infection when young patients with exposure to rodents (outdoor activities) present with high fever, thrombocytopenia grid severe lumbalgia. Hantavirus-serology is today available in almost all laboratories and antibody-detection is most reliable by recombinant antigen.","Acute renal failure; Emerging virurs; Hantavirus; Puumala","acute kidney failure; fever; hantavirus; hantavirus pulmonary syndrome; human; low back pain; nonhuman; respiratory distress; review; RNA virus infection; thrombocytopenia; virus transmission",,,,,,"Becker, C., Goubeaud, G., Zeier, M., Zöller, L., Hantavirusinfektionen und chronische Niereninsuffizienz (1993) Med. Welt, 44, pp. 569-573; Duchin, J.S., Koser, F.T., Peters, C.J., Hantavirus pulmonary syndrome: A clinical description of 17 patients with a newly recognized disease (1994) N. Engl. J. Med., 330, pp. 949-955; Gött, P., Zöller, L., Yang, S., Antigenicity of hantavirus nucleocapsid proteins expressed in E. coli (1991) Virus Research, 16, pp. 1-16; Huggins, J.W., Hsiang, C.M., Cosgriff, T.M., Prospective, double-blind, concurrent placebo-controlled clinical trial of intravenous ribavirin therapy of hemorrhagic fever with renal syndrome (1991) J. Infect. Dis., 164, p. 1119; Kim, G.R., Lee, Y.T., Park, C.H., A new natural reservoir of hantavirus: Isolation of hantaviruses of lung tissues of bats (1994) Arch. Virol., 134, pp. 85-95; Lähdevirta, J., Nephropathia epidemica in Finland. A clinical histological and epidemiological study (1971) Ann. Clin. Res., 3 (8 SUPPL.), pp. 1-154; Lee, H.W., Lee, P.W., Johnson, K.M., Isolation of the etiologic agent of Korean hemorrhagic fever (1978) J. Infect. Dis., 137, pp. 298-308; Linderholm, M., Billström, A., Settergren, B., Tärovik, A., Pulmonary involvement in nephropathia epidemica as demonstrated by computed tomography (1992) Infection, 5, pp. 263-266; Linderholm, M., Settergren, B., Aklin, C., A Swedish fatal case of nephropathia epidemica (1991) Scand. J. Infect. Dis., 23, pp. 501-502; Morse, S.S., (1993) Emerging Viruses, , Oxford University Press, Oxford; Morzunov, S.P., Feldmann, H., Spiropoulou, C.F., A newly recognized virus associated with a fatal case of hanta